						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Tiruppālēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and fragmentary. Seems to register the provision made for the sacred bath and offerings to the deities Śambhu and Dēvī, on the full moon day of Kārttīka by Nārāyaṇa, son of Venkaṭādri and Lakshmi of the Hārīta-gōtra and of Sāḷuva family. In characters of the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
